This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring November 9, 2011, as World Freedom Day. The proclamation commemorates the fall of the Berlin Wall in 1989, highlighting it as a symbol of the resilience of the human spirit and the triumph of freedom over tyranny. It also mentions the current wave of democratic movements in the Middle East and North Africa and expresses support for those who seek universal rights and a better future. The proclamation calls for honoring the brave individuals who tear down barriers to democracy and justice and reaffirms the commitment to freedom and democracy.